  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nested agents are agents that invoke other compiled agent graphs as sub-routines. The outer agent (root) calls an inner subgraph, waits for it to complete, and incorporates its result \u2014 just as you would call a function. This composition model lets you build complex pipelines from independently testable units and reuse inner subgraphs across multiple outer pipelines without copying code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Nested agents: root agent invokes inner subgraph containing inner supervisor and workers; result returns to root"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nesting vs. Delegation vs. Subgraphs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "These three terms overlap but have distinct meanings in a LangGraph context:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Subgraph"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 a compiled StateGraph registered as a node in a parent graph. State does not automatically flow between parent and child; you must explicitly map fields."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Delegation"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 transfers authority and scope; the delegatee operates autonomously and returns a typed result."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Nesting"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " \u2014 composition: the outer agent calls the inner subgraph synchronously, receives its full result, and continues. No scope transfer semantics required."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Registering a Subgraph as a Node"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LangGraph accepts a compiled subgraph anywhere a node function is expected. The subgraph's input state type must be compatible with the dict passed by the parent node, and the subgraph's output dict must be compatible with the parent's state update."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langgraph.graph import StateGraph, END\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\nfrom typing import TypedDict, Annotated\nimport operator\n\nhaiku  = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\nsonnet = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-sonnet-5\")\n\n# --- Inner subgraph: handles retrieval ---\nclass RetrievalState(TypedDict):\n    query: str\n    web_result: str\n    doc_result: str\n    errors: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n\ndef web_node(state: RetrievalState) -> dict:\n    try:\n        resp = haiku.invoke([\n            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"Return web search results for this query.\"},\n            {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": state[\"query\"]},\n        ])\n        return {\"web_result\": resp.content}\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\"web_result\": \"\", \"errors\": [f\"web:{exc}\"]}\n\ndef doc_node(state: RetrievalState) -> dict:\n    try:\n        resp = haiku.invoke([\n            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"Return relevant document excerpts for this query.\"},\n            {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": state[\"query\"]},\n        ])\n        return {\"doc_result\": resp.content}\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return {\"doc_result\": \"\", \"errors\": [f\"doc:{exc}\"]}\n\ndef build_retrieval_subgraph():\n    sg = StateGraph(RetrievalState)\n    sg.add_node(\"web\", web_node)\n    sg.add_node(\"doc\", doc_node)\n    sg.set_entry_point(\"web\")\n    sg.add_edge(\"web\", \"doc\")\n    sg.add_edge(\"doc\", END)\n    return sg.compile()\n\nretrieval_subgraph = build_retrieval_subgraph()\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Calling the Subgraph from the Outer Graph"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "class OuterState(TypedDict):\n    task: str\n    retrieval_web: str\n    retrieval_doc: str\n    answer: str\n    errors: Annotated[list[str], operator.add]\n\ndef call_retrieval(state: OuterState) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Wrapper node: maps outer state \u2192 subgraph input, runs subgraph, maps result back.\"\"\"\n    result = retrieval_subgraph.invoke({\n        \"query\":      state[\"task\"],\n        \"web_result\": \"\",\n        \"doc_result\": \"\",\n        \"errors\":     [],\n    })\n    return {\n        \"retrieval_web\": result[\"web_result\"],\n        \"retrieval_doc\": result[\"doc_result\"],\n        \"errors\":        result.get(\"errors\", []),\n    }\n\ndef answer_node(state: OuterState) -> dict:\n    context = f\"Web: {state['retrieval_web']}\\nDocs: {state['retrieval_doc']}\"\n    resp = sonnet.invoke([\n        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"Answer the question using the provided context.\"},\n        {\"role\": \"user\",   \"content\": f\"Question: {state['task']}\\nContext: {context}\"},\n    ])\n    return {\"answer\": resp.content}\n\ndef build_outer_graph():\n    builder = StateGraph(OuterState)\n    builder.add_node(\"retrieval\", call_retrieval)\n    builder.add_node(\"answer\",    answer_node)\n    builder.set_entry_point(\"retrieval\")\n    builder.add_edge(\"retrieval\", \"answer\")\n    builder.add_edge(\"answer\", END)\n    return builder.compile()\n\npipeline = build_outer_graph()\nresult = pipeline.invoke({\n    \"task\": \"What are the main risks of agentic AI systems?\",\n    \"retrieval_web\": \"\", \"retrieval_doc\": \"\", \"answer\": \"\", \"errors\": [],\n})\nprint(result[\"answer\"])\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "State Mapping Patterns"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The wrapper node pattern (a thin Python function that maps parent state to subgraph input and maps output back) is the safest approach. It makes the interface explicit and prevents the subgraph's internal field names from leaking into the outer state schema."
          }
        ]
      },
